---
By: Plutarch
Source:
  ID: 57c5499b-c3b2-4b09-92a9-a6e977a32050
  Locus:
    Page: 371
    Verse: 8
Tags:
  - Power
---
Power is of two kinds. One is obtained by the fear of punishment and the
other by the art of love. Power based on love is a thousand times more
effective and permanent than the one derived from fear of punishment.
